  "issue_title": "[Refactor] inline find_solver_from_timeline into check_github_issue_closed",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n`find_solver_from_timeline` in `gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py` is a thin wrapper around `find_solver_from_cross_references` with no unique behavior beyond a debug log. It currently has a single internal caller (`check_github_issue_closed`) and no other in-tree production callers.\n\nProposed change:\n- Inline `find_solver_from_cross_references(...)` directly in `check_github_issue_closed`.\n- Move `bt.logging.debug(f'Finding solver for {repo}#{issue_number}')` into `check_github_issue_closed`.\n- Remove `find_solver_from_timeline`.\n- Remove the delegation-only test class `TestFindSolverFromTimeline` and keep existing `TestFindSolverFromCrossReferences` coverage.\n\n## Motivation\n\nThis wrapper adds an extra layer without adding behavior, which increases maintenance cost and test noise. Inlining simplifies the solver lookup path and keeps the API surface focused on the real implementation (`find_solver_from_cross_references`), which is already used directly elsewhere (for example, `validator/issue_discovery/repo_scan.py`).\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-21T14:59:00.000Z",
